President Biden honors American veterans and acknowledges the personal connection his family has to Veterans Day. He pledges to continue the work of returning prisoners of war and missing in action soldiers, as well as remembering the sacrifice of their families. President Biden signed the PACT Act, which expands benefits and services for veterans, including funding new facilities and providing care and compensation for veterans exposed to toxic substances. He also highlights other bills signed to improve healthcare for veterans and the efforts made to address veteran suicide and homelessness. President Biden emphasizes the importance of inclusivity and safety for all service members, regardless of gender identity, sexual orientation, race, or religious background. He calls on Americans to honor veterans by putting service before self and working to build a better nation. The proclamation establishes November 11, 2022, as Veterans Day and encourages ceremonies and prayers to recognize the valor, courage, and sacrifice of veterans.